5 SECTION 2. BANK OF NORTH DAKOTA - LINE OF CREDIT - VALUE-ADDED MILK
6 PROCESSING FACILITY INCENTIVE PROGRAM. If the agriculture diversification and
7 development committee approves a grant under this Act, the agriculture commissioner may
8 borrow up to $5,000,000 through a line of credit from the Bank of North Dakota for deposit in
9 the agriculture diversification and development fund during the biennium beginning July 1,
10 2025, and ending June 30, 2027. The interest rate associated with the line of credit must be the
11 prevailing interest rate charged to North Dakota governmental entities. If the agriculture
12 commissioner accesses the line of credit, the agriculture commissioner shall request a
13 deficiency appropriation from the seventieth legislative assembly to repay the line of credit.
